<plot>David Bianchi, a performance poet and director Daniel J. Pico join forces to depict the inner struggle of a soldier suffering from the loss of a fallen comrade at the front lines of the Iraq War. The narrative is told in performance poetry and Gaelic verse that taps the psyche of a man in the extremest of human conditions: the grim realities of loss and war.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?505001</url></doc>
